text: Custer County is a county found in the U.S. state of Montana. As of the 2020 census, there were 11,867 people. Its county seat is Miles City. The county was formed in 1877 and named in honor of George Armstrong Custer. == References == Category:Montana counties Category:19th-century establishments in Montana Category:1877 establishments in the United States
title: Custer County, Montana
